<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="413" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="413">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="413">
This new species can be easily recognized by the absence of processes on the median portion of tergum X, inferior appendages with ventromesal process indistinct laterally and distinct ventrally with subtruncated apex, and Y-shaped phallotremal sclerite in lateral view. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silva Pereira &amp; Oliveira &amp; Desidério &amp; Calor &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Notalina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notalina ralphi" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ralphi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">Notalina ralphi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. franciscana" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franciscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">N. franciscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the subtruncate mesoventral process of the inferior appendages in ventral view. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. ralphi" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ralphi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">N. ralphi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. has the acuminate preanal appendages, which in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. franciscana" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franciscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">N. franciscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clavate. In addition, in the new species the ventrolateral margin of the segment X has stout, short setae, whereas 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="N." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="N. franciscana" order="Trichoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franciscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">N. franciscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has these setae only in the apex of the tergum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="413" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="413">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">Male.</emphasis>
Head brown (in alcohol) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (INPA) A lateral habitus B head, dorsal view C head and thorax, dorsal view D forewing, right dorsal view E hind wing, right dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (B); 0.5 mm (C); 2 mm (A, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713407" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">1B</figureCitation>
); maxillary and labial palps brown; antennae pale brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (INPA) A lateral habitus B head, dorsal view C head and thorax, dorsal view D forewing, right dorsal view E hind wing, right dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (B); 0.5 mm (C); 2 mm (A, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713407" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">1A</figureCitation>
). Thorax brown; pleuron pale brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (INPA) A lateral habitus B head, dorsal view C head and thorax, dorsal view D forewing, right dorsal view E hind wing, right dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (B); 0.5 mm (C); 2 mm (A, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713407" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">1C</figureCitation>
). Forewing brown, with small hyaline spot at thyridial cell; forewing length 7.8 mm (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">n</emphasis>
= 4), forks I and V present (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (INPA) A lateral habitus B head, dorsal view C head and thorax, dorsal view D forewing, right dorsal view E hind wing, right dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (B); 0.5 mm (C); 2 mm (A, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713407" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">1D</figureCitation>
); hind wing length 6 mm (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">n</emphasis>
= 4), forks I, III, and V present, fork I very narrow and fork III with very short petiole (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (INPA) A lateral habitus B head, dorsal view C head and thorax, dorsal view D forewing, right dorsal view E hind wing, right dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (B); 0.5 mm (C); 2 mm (A, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713407" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">1E</figureCitation>
). Legs pale brown; tibial spur formula 2, 2, 4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (INPA) A lateral habitus B head, dorsal view C head and thorax, dorsal view D forewing, right dorsal view E hind wing, right dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (B); 0.5 mm (C); 2 mm (A, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713407" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">1A</figureCitation>
). Segment IX, in lateral view, broadest ventrolaterally, anterior margin slightly sinuous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2A</figureCitation>
); apicodorsal area with paired, poorly developed, distantly situated protuberance; posterolateral margin bearing setae. Preanal appendages setose, long, and slender, ~ 2/3 length of segment X (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2A, B</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, apex acuminated towards inner margin, bearing long setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2B</figureCitation>
). Segment X, in lateral view, saddle-shaped; anterodorsal area slightly convex; mid-dorsal area without lateral protuberance; distal area without dorsomesal and dorsolateral processes; apicolateral processes rounded, bearing short stout setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2A</figureCitation>
); in dorsal view, V-shaped apicomesal incision extending anteriorly ~ 1/3 length of segment X; with a row of 5-7 short stout setae subapically. Inferior appendage, in lateral view, with broad basal portion, apical portion elongate, digitate, setose; basodorsal process rounded, smaller than basoventral process; dorsomesal process long and broad, apex acute, directed apicodorsad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2A</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, basoventral process well developed, slightly asymmetrical, rounded, apex directed mesad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2C</figureCitation>
); ventromesal process, in lateral view, indistinct (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2A</figureCitation>
); in ventral view, distinct with subtruncated apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2C</figureCitation>
). Phallic apparatus with a pair of strongly sclerotized, acuminate phallobase flanges, apex directed dorsad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2D</figureCitation>
); phallotremal sclerite well developed, roughly Y-shaped in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2D</figureCitation>
), with an anteriorly directed projection when viewed ventrally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Notalina (Neonotalina) ralphi sp. nov., male genitalia, holotype A lateral view B dorsal view C ventral view D phallic apparatus, lateral view E phallic apparatus, ventral view. Abbreviations: bdp, basodorsal process; bvp, basoventral process; mdp, mesodorsal process." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1111.77581.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/713408" pageId="0" pageNumber="413">2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
